            <h2>1️⃣ <strong>Technical Risks</strong></h2>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Compatibility Issues</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>Library may not be compatible with the current framework, language version, or operating system.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Breaking changes when upgrading to newer versions.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Performance Overhead</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>External libraries can introduce unnecessary memory usage or slow down the application.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Inefficient algorithms within the library may cause bottlenecks.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Hidden Bugs or Poor Quality</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>Undiscovered bugs in the library may cause crashes or data corruption.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Lack of proper unit testing or code reviews by the library maintainers.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Dependency Hell</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>Conflicts between versions of transitive dependencies (other libraries the library relies on).</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Hard-to-resolve dependency chains.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <hr>
            <h2>2️⃣ <strong>Security Risks</strong></h2>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Vulnerabilities in the Library</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>The library could contain known or unknown security flaws.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Slow patching by the maintainers increases exposure.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Supply Chain Attacks</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>Risk of malicious code injection if the package is compromised in the registry (e.g., NPM, PyPI, NuGet).</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Typosquatting attacks (e.g., installing a malicious package with a similar name).</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Unverified Source or Integrity</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>No cryptographic verification of downloaded binaries.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>No signed releases or checksums.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <hr>
            <h2>3️⃣ <strong>Maintenance &amp; Support Risks</strong></h2>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Abandonment Risk</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>The library may no longer be maintained or updated.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Maintainers may stop providing security patches or compatibility updates.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Poor Documentation</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>Insufficient or outdated documentation can make integration and debugging difficult.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Lack of Community/Support</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>Small or inactive community makes it hard to get help when issues arise.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Few contributors mean slower fixes.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <hr>
            <h2>4️⃣ <strong>Licensing &amp; Legal Risks</strong></h2>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>License Compatibility</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>The library&rsquo;s license (e.g., GPL, AGPL) might conflict with your project&rsquo;s license or distribution model.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Legal restrictions on commercial use.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Intellectual Property (IP) Risks</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>Potential copyright infringement if the library uses code from other projects without proper authorization.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <hr>
            <h2>5️⃣ <strong>Operational Risks</strong></h2>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Vendor/Service Lock-In</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>Over-dependence on a single vendor or closed-source library makes migration difficult if support ends.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Upgrade &amp; Migration Complexity</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>Future major version upgrades may require significant code changes.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Lack of backward compatibility.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Integration Complexity</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>Library may require complex configuration, which increases setup time and potential for misconfiguration.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <hr>
            <h2>✅ <strong>Mitigation Strategies</strong></h2>
            <p>To reduce these risks:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Security &amp; Compliance</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>Use tools like <strong>OWASP Dependency-Check</strong>, <strong>npm audit</strong>, <strong>Snyk</strong>, or <strong>GitHub Dependabot</strong> to monitor vulnerabilities.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Verify package integrity using hashes/signatures.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Maintenance &amp; Quality</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>Check GitHub activity (stars, forks, commits) and issue resolution speed.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Prefer libraries with active contributors and regular releases.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Version Management</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
